## TL;DR: What Every Cushion Solitaire Buyer Must Know First

A cushion cut diamond solitaire ring places one cushion-shaped diamond in a prong setting with no accent stones — the purest possible format for showcasing the stone's soft corner geometry, its table character, and its sparkle sub-type. Settings start at [$1,000 for the Petite Solitaire in 14K white gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (1,020 reviews); the most popular complete build is a [GIA 1ct G-VS1 cushion at $1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) paired with the [Classic Four Prong Solitaire Platinum at $1,180](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for **$3,071 total**. **→ Best first pick: [Classic Four Prong Solitaire Platinum at $1,180](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194156?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — the most-reviewed solitaire setting on Blue Nile (1,643 reviews), never needs replating, and shows the full cushion outline exactly as the shape was designed to be seen.**

**The Prong Paradox:** Most buyers assume 8-prong is the safer, better-looking choice for a cushion solitaire — more grip, more security, more stone coverage. The reality is the opposite. 4-prong leaves the cushion's soft rounded corners fully exposed, which is the defining visual quality of the cushion shape. 8-prong places additional prongs at the mid-sides, interrupting the corner outline and making the cushion read closer to a round brilliant — you paid for a cushion and end up obscuring its most distinctive feature.

